<i>♪ Love is a drug ♪</i>

30:11.592 --> 30:13.420
We should go out.

30:13.507 --> 30:16.510
I think I told you about
my sunlight allergy, right?

30:18.077 --> 30:19.513
Is that a new umbrella?

30:19.600 --> 30:21.820
What happened to your parasol?

30:21.907 --> 30:23.560
I lost it.

30:23.647 --> 30:26.346
We could go to the park
or our favorite bench.

30:26.433 --> 30:28.478
We have night shifts, so...

30:28.565 --> 30:30.959
We could,
but I'm just so happy

30:31.046 --> 30:32.787
being here with you.

30:32.874 --> 30:35.050
Except for all the times
you mysteriously dash off

30:35.137 --> 30:36.486
and leave me.

30:36.573 --> 30:38.445
I have a very strict
workout regimen

30:38.532 --> 30:42.275
that requires all my focus
and dedication.

30:48.324 --> 30:50.849
Whoa!
Reginald, are you okay?

30:50.936 --> 30:52.111
I'll be right back.

31:00.684 --> 31:02.773
What's wrong?

31:14.742 --> 31:16.700
Hello, Todd.

31:16.787 --> 31:18.615
Every time I go for a run,

31:18.702 --> 31:21.531
I end up running here,

31:21.618 --> 31:23.533
but I don't know why I do that.

31:23.620 --> 31:25.231
That feeling will fade.

31:25.318 --> 31:26.972
Trust me.

31:27.059 --> 31:30.236
I trust you more
than any person I've ever met,

31:30.323 --> 31:33.326
which is weird, right?

31:33.413 --> 31:36.242
I mean,
I don't even know your name.

31:36.329 --> 31:37.939
Maurice.

31:38.026 --> 31:40.594
Hi, Maurice.

31:40.681 --> 31:42.857
Goodbye, Todd.

31:42.944 --> 31:46.382
Uh, can I come in, please?

31:46.469 --> 31:48.210
No.

31:48.297 --> 31:50.343
Not today.
Not in your current condition.

31:50.430 --> 31:51.735
Next time I go for a run,

31:51.822 --> 31:53.781
I'm gonna end up running
right back here,

31:53.868 --> 31:55.565
no matter what I try to do.

31:55.652 --> 31:56.958
I know.

32:08.883 --> 32:10.015
What?

32:20.242 --> 32:21.330
Is this weird?

32:21.417 --> 32:23.245
I bathe multiple times a day.

32:23.332 --> 32:24.507
No, I mean us.

32:24.594 --> 32:27.510
Us is perfect.
Don't you think?

32:27.597 --> 32:29.425
Well, I don't really know
anything about you

32:29.512 --> 32:33.255
except that Angela hired you
to kill me, but you didn't.

32:33.342 --> 32:35.997
What do you wanna know
about me, roundish lover?

32:36.084 --> 32:38.478
Something unbelievable.

32:38.565 --> 32:42.743
I have 222 secrets.

32:45.615 --> 32:46.921
Tell me one of them.

32:52.709 --> 32:54.885
Once upon a time,

32:54.973 --> 32:58.150
a fearsome vampire, Logan,
decided he was made

32:58.237 --> 33:00.891
for the bigger
and bestest things,

33:00.979 --> 33:03.546
but his great rival, Abraham,

33:03.633 --> 33:07.333
held the utmost deacon
of the Americas.

33:07.420 --> 33:09.596
Abraham was
a vampire of legend,

33:09.683 --> 33:11.554
oldest of our kind,

33:11.641 --> 33:15.341
one possessed
of unimaginable powers.

33:15.428 --> 33:19.258
Abraham could turn a vampire
back to human,

33:19.345 --> 33:21.738
like a God
or an angel might do.

33:24.089 --> 33:26.961
Logan hired me
and my partner, Stanley,

33:27.048 --> 33:29.920
to find Abraham
and kill him deader than dirt.

33:30.008 --> 33:32.706
Stanley was vicious.

33:32.793 --> 33:35.317
And kind.

33:35.404 --> 33:37.450
He had white patch in his hair,
and nobody called him "Patchy,"

33:37.537 --> 33:38.494
and that's sad.

33:41.019 --> 33:43.891
We found Abraham
in a place far from here

33:43.978 --> 33:46.285
called Spokane, Washington.

33:46.372 --> 33:49.201
Stanley went ahead,
as was our custom.

33:51.377 --> 33:54.467
He was truly
the best killer-diller of all.

33:56.512 --> 34:00.038
But Stanley was lost that day

34:00.125 --> 34:02.997
and never found.

34:03.084 --> 34:05.173
And I was trapped
by phantoms, and ghosts,

34:05.260 --> 34:09.177
and everything upside down,

34:09.264 --> 34:11.049
so I ran away
from that haunted place

34:11.136 --> 34:14.530
as fast as my feet could run.

34:14.617 --> 34:17.098
Phantoms and ghosts?

34:17.185 --> 34:20.275
I was afraid.

34:20.362 --> 34:22.930
I've never been afraid
a single time since that day,

34:23.017 --> 34:26.586
but I will never
forget the feeling.

34:29.197 --> 34:30.590
On the plus side,

34:30.677 --> 34:33.114
Abraham was never
heard from again,

34:33.201 --> 34:35.290
and Logan
took his council seat,

34:35.377 --> 34:38.815
and maybe Stanley
did not die for nothing.

34:38.902 --> 34:40.469
The end.

34:46.823 --> 34:51.045
I have 221 secrets.

34:53.221 --> 34:55.441
What's the sitch
with Reginald?

34:55.528 --> 34:57.138
He's supposed to be here.
I don't know what happened.

34:59.706 --> 35:01.708
All right, there you go. Cheers.

35:01.795 --> 35:03.405
Have you ever felt like
something happened to you,

35:03.492 --> 35:04.972
but it didn't happen
at the same time,

35:05.059 --> 35:07.366
but you have no idea
why you feel like that?

35:07.453 --> 35:08.758
All the time.

35:10.630 --> 35:13.023
I would very much like
to purchase a delicious slushy

35:13.111 --> 35:14.547
for my new lover.

35:24.165 --> 35:27.168
Does your new lover
have a favorite flavor?

35:27.255 --> 35:29.779
As a matter of fact,
beverage servant,

35:29.866 --> 35:32.739
nothing tickles his taste buds
like a Pineapple Surprise.

35:50.974 --> 35:52.454
Hey, Sarah!

35:52.541 --> 35:53.847
You read my mind.

35:53.934 --> 35:55.327
How did you do that?

35:55.414 --> 35:57.503
Three is truly
the happiest number.

35:57.590 --> 35:58.982
In case you're wondering,
I'm referring

35:59.069 --> 36:00.375
to the three-way
we're about to have--

36:00.462 --> 36:02.203
you, me, and Reginald.

36:02.290 --> 36:03.813
And if that's not
the stairway to heaven,

36:03.900 --> 36:06.164
I don't know what Page
and Plant were thinking.

36:13.345 --> 36:14.694
No. No, wait.

36:14.781 --> 36:15.956
Sarah, wait!

36:18.306 --> 36:20.265
Well, that's not
what I had in mind at all.

36:24.182 --> 36:25.748
Please, Sarah, wait.

36:25.835 --> 36:26.923
I can explain.

36:27.010 --> 36:28.664
Leave me alone.

36:28.751 --> 36:30.362
But it's not
what it looks like.

36:30.449 --> 36:31.711
I--I mean, it's partially
what it looks like,

36:31.798 --> 36:32.886
but it's not as bad
as it seems.

36:32.973 --> 36:35.367
I knew something was wrong,

36:35.454 --> 36:37.586
but God damn it, Reginald,
I didn't even consider--

36:37.673 --> 36:39.980
No, we can turn back time, okay?

36:40.067 --> 36:42.069
I can make this go away.

36:42.156 --> 36:44.680
What the hell
are you talking about?

36:44.767 --> 36:47.074
Pretend?
I would never--

36:47.161 --> 36:48.945
Listen to me!

36:49.032 --> 36:50.469
Forget what you saw
in the hotel room.

36:50.556 --> 36:52.427
Forget Nikki.
Forget me.

36:52.514 --> 36:54.777
You never came here.

36:54.864 --> 36:56.562
You left work,
but you came back,

36:56.649 --> 36:58.520
and you have no memory
of where you were

36:58.607 --> 37:01.349
until you see me again, and
everything will be wonderful.

37:03.003 --> 37:05.527
Sure, Reginald.

37:05.614 --> 37:07.529
I can do that.

37:07.616 --> 37:10.532
I'll forget what I saw
in the hotel room.

37:10.619 --> 37:12.969
I'll forget Nikki.

37:13.056 --> 37:14.841
I'll go back to work,
and I'll have no memory

37:14.928 --> 37:18.279
of where I was
until you see me again,

37:18.366 --> 37:20.412
and everything
will be wonderful.

37:21.630 --> 37:24.459
But most of all...

37:24.546 --> 37:27.157
I'll forget you.

37:27.245 --> 37:28.463
Wait, Sarah. Wait.

37:28.550 --> 37:30.422
Aah!

37:30.509 --> 37:32.424
Where did you get
that bracelet?

37:32.511 --> 37:34.121
Maurice gave it to me.

37:34.208 --> 37:36.428
Hey, Sarah.

37:36.515 --> 37:38.212
What are you doing here?

37:38.299 --> 37:40.301
I've got a very important
appointment with Nikki.

37:40.388 --> 37:43.609
She's a vampire too.
Did you know that?

37:43.696 --> 37:45.959
Dude, you look like
someone beat your dog to death

37:46.046 --> 37:47.265
with your cat.

37:50.398 --> 37:51.573
Hey, Nikki.

37:53.575 --> 37:55.403
Nikki, wait up.
Where are you going?

37:55.490 --> 37:57.100
When I make a mistake,

37:57.187 --> 37:58.232
I don't fail to make
the biggest one possible,

37:58.319 --> 37:59.625
and I like that about myself.

37:59.712 --> 38:01.191
It keeps things interesting,

38:01.279 --> 38:04.064
but you lied to me,
and you lied to her!

38:04.151 --> 38:06.719
You are a bad toy.

38:06.806 --> 38:09.461
You are not my dream lover.

38:09.548 --> 38:14.292
You are not the song
the angels sing.

38:14.379 --> 38:16.859
Maurice Miller
was right about you.

38:16.946 --> 38:18.644
You're not one of us.

38:18.731 --> 38:20.950
Not yet.

38:21.037 --> 38:22.517
You're still full of human,

38:22.604 --> 38:24.998
and I have
zero tolerance policy for that.

38:25.085 --> 38:26.129
I eat humans.

38:26.216 --> 38:28.088
I do not let them eat me.

38:28.175 --> 38:31.178
Also, I'm bored

38:31.265 --> 38:33.049
and do not wanna play
with you anymore.

38:33.136 --> 38:34.790
Wait.
You can't just go.

38:34.877 --> 38:36.139
Not now. Please.

38:38.751 --> 38:40.361
I'm sorry, little human.

38:40.448 --> 38:42.494
I can't help you.

38:42.581 --> 38:45.061
But maybe
that's best for everyone.

38:47.455 --> 38:48.761
What did you do?

38:48.848 --> 38:50.589
You ruined everything.

38:50.676 --> 38:52.678
- It doesn't matter.
- Nikki was gonna help me.

38:52.765 --> 38:54.244
She was gonna turn me
into a vampire

38:54.332 --> 38:55.463
so I can fight evil.

38:55.550 --> 38:57.073
Claire, stop!

38:57.160 --> 38:58.858
Look at me.

38:58.945 --> 39:00.816
Is this the life you want?

39:00.903 --> 39:02.035
How does eternity look
to you now?

39:02.122 --> 39:04.342
Because trust me,

39:04.429 --> 39:06.169
it's not all
it's worked up to be.

39:06.256 --> 39:08.781
It's blood, and hunger,

39:08.868 --> 39:13.046
and you have no------- idea
what it feels like.

39:13.133 --> 39:15.004
And right now,
the last thing I need

39:15.091 --> 39:17.311
is a disappointed fangirl who
didn't get fangs for Christmas.

39:19.922 --> 39:21.924
Asshole.

39:31.934 --> 39:35.460
I can't be out.

39:35.547 --> 39:37.157
There's got
to be blood somewhere.

39:47.210 --> 39:50.649
Dude,
where the hell have you been?

39:50.736 --> 39:52.390
Are you drunk?

39:52.477 --> 39:54.043
God.

39:54.130 --> 39:55.480
No, no, no, no, wait.

39:55.567 --> 39:57.307
Cheeseburger overdose.

39:57.395 --> 39:59.875
Yeah,
it's entirely possible for you.

39:59.962 --> 40:01.094
You know what you are?

40:01.181 --> 40:03.009
You're a disease.

40:03.096 --> 40:05.054
You're making everybody sick
around you.

40:05.141 --> 40:07.492
Note to self:

40:07.579 --> 40:08.884
take Reginald's
Employee of the Month photo

40:08.971 --> 40:09.972
and throw it in the trash.

40:10.059 --> 40:11.539
Listen to me!

40:11.626 --> 40:13.628
I'm gonna drink your blood,

40:13.715 --> 40:15.848
and that fills you
with joy and happiness.

40:30.036 --> 40:31.646
Todd?

40:31.733 --> 40:33.039
--!----!----!

40:37.696 --> 40:39.349
Hello? Help!

40:39.437 --> 40:41.090
Something horrible happened
at the Slushy Shack!

40:41.177 --> 40:43.484
Hurry!
I--I need your help!

40:54.582 --> 40:55.540
-- you!

40:55.627 --> 40:56.715
I could've handled this.

40:56.802 --> 40:58.107
I would have.

40:58.194 --> 40:59.108
You decided
to teach me a lesson

40:59.195 --> 41:01.154
for some------- reason.

41:01.241 --> 41:03.199
You opened your big mouth
to Nikki

41:03.286 --> 41:05.941
and you give Sarah
that bracelet.

41:06.028 --> 41:07.813
You turn me,

41:07.900 --> 41:10.119
and then you wreck me.

41:10.206 --> 41:11.643
Why?

41:11.730 --> 41:14.472
Why would you do that to me?

41:14.559 --> 41:16.256
Wasn't I good enough for you?

41:16.343 --> 41:18.214
Wasn't I a good enough man
for you to trust?

41:23.872 --> 41:26.614
I lost Sarah.

41:26.701 --> 41:28.616
I lost Claire.

41:28.703 --> 41:31.053
I lost Nikki.

41:31.140 --> 41:33.186
I killed Todd.

41:35.318 --> 41:38.539
I'm a liar and an asshole

41:38.626 --> 41:41.977
and a murderer,

41:42.064 --> 41:43.979
but that's all on you.

41:54.120 --> 41:57.036
<i>♪ You're pretty
when you sleep ♪</i>

41:57.123 --> 41:59.865
<i>♪ Like frozen memories ♪</i>

41:59.952 --> 42:02.694
<i>♪ I hold inside my mind ♪</i>

42:02.781 --> 42:05.653
<i>♪ When I can't sleep
at night ♪</i>

42:05.740 --> 42:08.351
<i>♪ I wanna say goodbye ♪</i>

42:08.438 --> 42:13.748
<i>♪ But if I do, you'll cry ♪</i>

42:15.315 --> 42:20.102
<i>♪ Please don't cry ♪</i>

42:21.626 --> 42:24.324
<i>♪ I think ♪</i>

42:24.411 --> 42:28.415
<i>♪ I'm gonna ♪</i>

42:28.502 --> 42:32.767
<i>♪ Cry ♪</i>

42:32.854 --> 42:38.468
<i>♪ I'm starting over ♪</i>

42:38.556 --> 42:41.602
<i>♪ Tonight ♪</i>

42:41.689 --> 42:43.952
<i>♪ Oh ♪</i>

42:46.868 --> 42:51.133
<i>♪ Anything and everything ♪</i>

42:51.220 --> 42:53.875
<i>♪ I'm thinking things ♪</i>

42:53.962 --> 42:56.486
<i>♪ That I should not think ♪</i>

42:56.574 --> 43:02.971
<i>♪ Oh, anything ♪</i>
